Tesla registers 61,800 Model 3s in October
NextBigFuture.com
paragraph:
Tesla had registered a total of 61,843 Model 3 VINs in October.Elon Musk noted that a ramp to 7,000 Model 3 per week should be doable just by optimizing its existing lines.To date, 69,712 dual motor VINs have been registered w/ NHTSA (excl. test batches). This represents ~56% of all VINs registered (123,551) since AWD registrations began on 6/28. 6/28 – 9/30: 74.9% AWD (47,880 of 63,905) 10/1 – 10/26: 36.6% AWD (21,832 of 59,646) pic.twitter.com/ZUl0VrcneN— Model 3 VINs (@Model3VINs) October 26, 2018#Tesla registered 2,297 new #Model3 VINs. ~30% estimated to be dual motor. Highest VIN is 179851. https://t.co/awxm6F91k2— Model 3 VINs (@Model3VINs) October 27, 2018#Tesla registered 13,629 new #Model3 VINs. ~0% estimated to be dual motor. Highest VIN is 169791. https://t.co/CbAbsrLRkz— Model 3 VINs (@Model3VINs) October 25, 2018
